      {
        "page": 1,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "Object pronouns replace the thing or",
          "person receiving the action.",
          "",
          "DIRECT OBJECT (what/whom):",
          "me = me              nos = us",
          "te = you             los/las = them",
          "lo = him/it          la = her/it",
          "",
          "¿Ves el libro? Sí, lo veo.",
          "(Do you see the book? Yes, I see it.)",
          "",
          "INDIRECT OBJECT (to/for whom):",
          "me = to me           nos = to us",
          "te = to you          les = to them",
          "le = to him/her",
          "",
          "Le doy el libro. (I give him the book.)",
          "The object pronoun goes BEFORE the verb"
        ],
        "pronunciation": "Lección trece",
        "pronunciation_mappings": {}
      },
      {
        "page": 2,
        "total_pages": 2,
        "content": [
          "Before conjugated verbs:             Press 1",
          "Lo quiero. (I want it.)",
          "Me gusta. (I like it.)",
          "",
          "Attached to infinitives:             Press 2",
          "Voy a decirte algo.",
          "(I'm going to tell you something.)",
          "Quiero comprarlo. (I want to buy it.)",
          "",
          "Attached to gerunds:                 Press 3",
          "Estoy haciéndolo. (I'm doing it.)",
          "",
          "Both positions are correct:          Press 4",
          "Lo quiero comprar = Quiero comprarlo",
          "",
          "Don't overthink placement. You'll",
          "develop a feel for it through the",
          "example sentences on the cards."
        ],
        "pronunciation_mappings": {
          "1": "lo quiero, me gusta",
          "2": "voy a decirte algo, quiero comprarlo",
          "3": "estoy haciéndolo",
          "4": "lo quiero comprar, quiero comprarlo"
        }
      }
    ]
